<paragraph id="6DF287868FBA74B845524715BCC30EA0" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">
The lectotype designation of 
<bibRefCitation id="61536141EF2F5280725DDB67F01393BD" author="Warncke, K" journalOrPublisher="Bollettino del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Venezia" pageId="0" pageNumber="35" pagination="67 - 166" refId="B75" refString="Warncke, K, 1982. Beitrag zur Bienenfauna des Iran. 14. Die Gattung Halictus Latr., mit Bemerkungen ueber unbekannte und neue Halictus -Arten in der Westpalaearktis und Zentralasien. Bollettino del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale di Venezia 32: 67 - 166" title="Beitrag zur Bienenfauna des Iran. 14. Die Gattung Halictus Latr., mit Bemerkungen ueber unbekannte und neue Halictus - Arten in der Westpalaearktis und Zentralasien." volume="32" year="1982">Warncke (1982</bibRefCitation>
: 147) is unnecessary as the species was described from a single female that was directly written about by 
<bibRefCitation id="5CD2F11B18D0D8718375AD4866AD71B1" author="Morawitz, F" journalOrPublisher="Izvestiya Imperatorskogo Obshchestva Lyubiteley Estestvoznaniya, Anthropologii i Ethnografii" pageId="0" pageNumber="35" pagination="161 - 303" refId="B52" refString="Morawitz, F, 1876. A Travel to Turkestan by the Member-Founder of the Society A.P. Fedtschenko, accomplished from the Imperial Society of Naturalists, Anthropologists, and Ethnographists on a Commission from the General-Governor of Turkestan K.P. von Kaufmann (Issue 13). Vol. II. Zoogeographical Investigations. Pt. V. (Division 7). Bees (Mellifera). Pt. II [Andrenidae]. Izvestiya Imperatorskogo Obshchestva Lyubiteley Estestvoznaniya, Anthropologii i Ethnografii 21 (3): 161 - 303" title="A Travel to Turkestan by the Member-Founder of the Society A. P. Fedtschenko, accomplished from the Imperial Society of Naturalists, Anthropologists, and Ethnographists on a Commission from the General-Governor of Turkestan K. P. von Kaufmann (Issue 13). Vol. II. Zoogeographical Investigations. Pt. V. (Division 7). Bees (Mellifera). Pt. II [Andrenidae]." volume="21" year="1876">Morawitz (1876</bibRefCitation>
: 235).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="EF7C26EC3B704CC22B7455672F2D3E1B" pageId="0" pageNumber="35">
